Pre-Game Insights: Harambee Stars coach Engin Firat expects a tough match against Cameroon, noting their aggressive and physical style of play.
Firat emphasizes the importance of a 180-minute plan, considering both home and away legs.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is the third in Group J of the 2025 AFCON qualifiers.
Kenya is aiming for maximum points to secure a better position in the qualifiers.
Others: Michael Olunga and Daniel Anyembe are key players returning from injuries or personal reasons.
Cameroon has a strong squad with notable players like Andre Onana and Bryan Mbeumo.
